76561198214912413,Recommended,408900,23882038,"Posted: 27 June, 2016",all,AnitaBandaid4x4,"Just over 5 hours in, and here are my two cents so far.PROS:Fun - ridiculously so.The layout of the maps remains unchanged from game to game, so you don't feel completely lost around the station of your choosing. The locations of the supply boxes and samples do change, which helps keep this re-playable without being confusing.They do have ""achievements"" of sorts, which help you get different types of helmet shields, abilities, etc. It also seems like these sorts of options/choices may be expanded in the future.The developers do interact with people playing or interested in playing their games, and from my experience so far, are very friendly and helpful.CONS:The game is so new that not many people are playing this yet, which is a bummer because it is hard to find other people to play against. If you play against bots, you will be the monster every time - bots can't be the monster (confirmed by Zag himself - thanks, Zag!) and you're it. However, when there are other humans on the server, the random choice of who plays the monster does add quite a bit.The tutorial is a lot of reading, and is not interactive at all. Moving was pretty straightforward, especially if you've played Minecraft with the default movement keys. However, if you want to learn how to use any of your abilities, you have to pay attention to the tutorial and the HUD, and use some trial and error to get the hang of it.Once I have more playtime under my belt, I may add more to this. Also, as development progresses, some of the above may change. For now, these are my first impressions."
