,Recommended,408900,22907029,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,blaccdixk,"EDIT 2: Recently I was actually able to get in some games and, over the course of a week or so, found that I was able to consistently get in games with minimal issues. There are still some remnants of the connectivity/loading issues mentioned previously, but the rate at which they appear has been diminished significantly. They might even have gone away entirely since the Sunny Side Up patch but I have not played since that patch was released so I can't verify entirely.But, that said, the bugs have been worked out to a point that I think is very acceptable for an Early Access game so I am changing this review to a positive! The games I was able to play were fantastic and filled with fun and tension. A lot of it depends on the people you play with, and the more talkative players you can get, the better. Playing as a Spaceman is a fun mix of paranoia and tension and the rounds are a good mix of winning and losing, depending on how the monster plays. There are also numerous ways to go about your objectives as the monster so it varies each round, which keeps things fresh. The 15 minute time limit is a perfect amount of time to get objectives done but also keep you constantly moving and preventing the game from stagnating. There are multiple maps, but all anyone ever plays on is Echo. I tried out some of the other maps but people just mostly complained until I changed it to Echo. That is another downside though is that the game doesn't exit back to lobby and there isn't a way to vote for a map change or even force change it yourself as host at the end of a round or set of rounds.The things I would recommend being aware of if you are a new player are the small playerbase (not a lot of people are on and you need to play in peak hours to find a game). Basically, don't expect to play outside of the hours of 7ish to midnight. Also, there is a bug (again, SSU patch may have fixed this) where servers will only list 1/31 players in the game, regardless of how many players are actually in it. So you have to join the game to see how active it is.I would also be aware of the crashing/joining/connection issues. They have, for me, almost gone away entirely, but your experience may vary. Also, again, keep in mind that a lot of your fun depends on other players. I have not had any bad experiences with the community, but as it continues to grow, this could change.Lastly, the pistol damage seems too small. Everyone starts with it though, so I get that it can't be too powerful, and the balance of heavy weapons on the map seems good because you don't want everyone powered up, but I got into a pistol duel with someone and we shot at each other for literally five straight minutes dancing around and neither one of us died and we eventually just ran in opposite directions. If you have just a pistol and are facing down the monster, it is better to just run.I don't want to end on a negative note so I will say this: this game has, I believe, a terrific future ahead of it. The devs somehow took a horror setting (imo) and, instead of it becoming less frightening with more players, it just gets scarier. That is an achievement in itself. That's not to say that you won't experience some goofy/funny moments, but the overall feeling is very tense and that is a big positive for a game like this. The devs also seem very active in their work on this. I gather from other reviews that there might be some bad blood from a previous project? I can't speak on that, but I can speak on what I've seen with this game and the updates come frequently and they seem to be very aware of the current issues, what needs to be done to fix them, and where the game is heading.I would definitely recommend buying this game. It is a unique multiplayer game that blends a lot of elements together in a wonderful way. The more people that play, the better the games get, so I would love to see more players involved. I'm typically very wary of Early Access games, but I can say that from what I have seen with this, it is at a point where you should feel safe investing your time and money into it. It is only going to get better. I hope to see a lot more of you Spacemen out there.------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------EDIT 1: I played the game since the new patch, and while the crashing problem has gone away, it seems to have been replaced with (or maybe this has always been a problem and I never got far enough to try it) connectivity/loading issues. Mainly, when trying to join, I will get to in-game screen and I can see other Spacemen running around, but will get no options to do anything. If it's not that, then I'll get sent to a black screen where it sticks in an infinite loading screen. Anytime this happens, I am forced to ALT+F4 out because there is no other recourse, so basically it went from crashing on its own to forcing me to crash it. I tried joining after the host sent the game back to the lobby, and I still got slammed into the never-loading start screen when the host started the game again.I managed to get into and play one game, which was fun (mostly bots, but a handful of real people). We lost due to the time limit, but I had a couple tense, close calls with the monster that were exciting. The gameplay is fun on its own, but the true experience seems like it will be heavily dependent on the people you play with. I am glad that my initial thoughts that it would be fun were validated by it actually being fun.Unfortunately, I have to leave the review as negative. The general instability as a whole is just too much to be able to overlook it, even in Early Access. Getting into one game out of six attempts is just no bueno. It is a good sign that patches seem to be coming out on a pretty quick basis though, and I have no doubt that eventually (and possibly very soon) this review will turn to Positive, but I just can't do it right now. If it were solely based on the gameplay, it'd already be a Positive, but if I can't get to the gameplay, then what's the point?------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ORIGINAL: The concept and gameplay look and sound fun from videos I watched from other people, but that is about all you are going to be able to do. It seems like luck of the draw whether or not the game will run for you. At any point, for any reason it feels like, the game will kick you back to the menu, or completely crash. This can happen in menus, in the lobby select, in-game waiting to start, in-game while you spawn, and just at any point in-game, period. This is even if the game will launch in the first place.There are numerous other bugs, things you would expect from an Early Access game, so I'm not going to list those. But when the game is near-completely unplayable, it should not be released in any form, at all. I have not once been able to complete a whole match, and the most I ever got to play of a match was three minutes.tl;dr DO NOT BUY THIS GAME. It has the potential to be something great, but that something will never exist in Early Access."
