76561198012160186,Recommended,408900,22898512,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,Dr. Rockso,"I'll start off by saying that at time of  writing this, the game is in Alpha.  I see tons of negative reviews praising the gameplay and concept, but crying the game is buggy and un-stable.  No sh!t.  The game is in Alpha, geniuses.With that said, this game is pretty hysterical, and I typically dislike FPS.  It's basically a 15-minute murder-mystery in space.  The best part is when you're the monster, and hearing the screams and surprise of murdering the spaceman you've been helping for the past three minutes, as he turns and see you suddenly morph.You can set traps (the air lock decompression is always satisfying) and you can sabotage the power, equipment, etc.  You got to be slick though, because if peeps see you acting weird ... blamo!  Much of the games charm also comes from the in-game voice-chat.  You have to be a little bit of a real-life actor to ""accidentally"" shoot, push people offa bridges, drop a flash bang or call people to a room to kill them one-by-one.The game is currenly $12.00.  It's buggy as hell, but it has great potential and well worth the price in it's current state.  I'd strongly reccomend supporting this one."
